Yes, you'll have to be inventive, to distinguish yourself at the Diamonds Club, and frivolity rules, so in a contest we cast pearls before swine in the adjoining parc of our family manor.
Bernard elucidates that salt is a scarce item in certain villages. Rat meat is meat that is seen as almost valueless, something that children sometimes eat; their proud catch of their common hunt. You don't « cast pearls before swine » and you will carefully store your precious possession for better, more suitable circumstances.
